<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Manalow Gottamed</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-11-06 01:43:41</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Ok folks, here's the scoop.  I have all of the rods except <BR>
for the one in Lower Guk, which requires either a massively <BR>
camped zone or high level help, and Everfrost (which I will <BR>
get when I am ready to complete the quest).  Not one death, <BR>
but a couple scares. The Graffe spoiler was fairly<BR>
useful, but a couple notes:  Azia - easy, try it later in <BR>
the norrathian evening, less sharks then apparently. I got <BR>
in without incident. Maybe luck, but never saw a shark. Beza - <BR>
not done yet (sorry). Caza - Lake rathe, get underwater <BR>
breathing and inch your way forward til you can get the rod, <BR>
then just turn around. Dena - cake, no need for enduring <BR>
breath, just swim straight from unrest and down, you'll hit it<BR>
Ena - guk, not done yet. Fana - Oasis, gobs on top floor<BR>
CANNOT see invis (just don't wander below, they'll agro). <BR>
Geza - Highpass. Cake, not guarded. Heda - Qeynos aquaducts, <BR>
not difficult per say, just hard to find. I recomment a guide <BR>
or a map. Izah - neriak. Good luck if you're not evil, I'm <BR>
agnostic so it was easy (no other pointers except what's been <BR>
mentioned already). Jaka - Unrest. No worries, fairly easy <BR>
just watch for a skeleton there. Good luck, the staff looks <BR>
very nice. <BR>
<BR>
Manalow Gottamed<BR>
Gnomes in Wonderland<BR>
Level 20<BR>
<BR>
"Nuke 'em til they glow, then shoot 'em in the dark"</font></td></tr></table>
