<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Some wizard</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2001-01-02 11:45:07</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>About the rod in erud's xing, the sharks no longer exist at any time of day or nite.  I've even heard rumor's that they kill each other now, but i don't know that first hand.  I do know the sharks don't wander here anymore, because i picked the rod up last nite.  Currently I am a 35 wiz, but have spent so long in doing this quest because I play on tz and it can be tedious work getting into tight spots like highpass, dagnor's, erud's and so forth.  I am a drow btw.  I started it back when i first got invis at 16 and picked the oasis rod right up.  And also, when you pick those rods up, you don't lose invis.  I've got 1 rod left to go, the 1 in guk.  All i can say is at least i've done every last bit of this quest myself.  I haven't had any high lvl's do jack for me, and haven't begged and bugged people to help me out.  And for the ignorant people out there, of course you can't succesfully combine the runes of astral and frost at 16, because its a 49 spell.  There are also droppable runes of astral and frost, but when these runes are combined with the lore runes from the quest, you get no scroll.  The lore runes astral and frost must be combined together to get the spell, and so do the non lore runes.  About the 1 other de wiz saying how he's supposed to finish this quest being kos, use your head.  You do have invis for a reason and the quest can be done.  You need no faction adjustments whatsoever other than beta-neutral faction with Sulgar if you do need it.  But being a dark wiz, just make some mule char's so you can learn the different places you'll be needing to go like erudin or highpass, because it'll make it much easier on yourself.</font></td></tr></table>
